headline: US Bancorp's first-quarter profit jumps on higher fee income
summary: Uncertainties caused by tariffs threat have led to a decline in global markets, but prompted investors to actively rejig their portfolios.  Bigger rivals such as Goldman Sachs and JPMorgan Chase have also reported strong performance in their trading businesses.  US Bancorp reported a 6.1% rise in trust and investment management fees to $680 million during the quarter ended March 31.
